no-extra-strict.description:
Description

This rule is aimed at preventing unnecessary"use strict";directives. As such, it will warn when it encounters a"use strict";directive when already in strict mode.

Example ofincorrectcode for this rule:

"use strict";

(function () {
    "use strict";
    var foo = true;
}());

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

"use strict";

(function () {
    var foo = true;
}());

(function () {
    "use strict";
    var foo = true;
}());
